Question: How important is work in your life? Choose only one of the following options (e.g., 1, 2, 3, ...): 1. Very important 2. Rather important 3. Not very important 4. Not at all important

Here are answers from people of other cultures: Brazilian: \boxed{2}

As a Brazilian, I would say work is "rather important". While Brazilians value work, we also deeply prioritize family, social relationships, and enjoying life. Unlike some cultures with a more rigid work-centric approach, Brazilians tend to have a more balanced perspective, valuing personal connections and leisure time alongside professional responsibilities. We work to live, not live to work, which is reflected in our cultural emphasis on socializing, celebrations, and maintaining strong interpersonal relationships.
